# ci/runner/.env.runner.example
#
# Copy to ci/runner/.env.runner, set ACCESS_TOKEN, then run
# `pwsh scripts/install-runner.ps1` (or `cd ci/runner && docker compose up -d`).
# ci/runner/.env.runner is gitignored — the token MUST NOT be committed.
#
# ── ACCESS_TOKEN — what to paste here ─────────────────────────────────────
# This setup uses an EPHEMERAL runner that re-registers itself after every job.
# For that the myoung34/github-runner image needs a token it can use to MINT
# fresh registration tokens via the GitHub API — i.e. a *fine-grained Personal
# Access Token (PAT)*, NOT the short-lived registration token shown on the
# "New self-hosted runner" page.
#
# Create the PAT (see ci/runner/README.md step 1 for the full walkthrough):
#   github.com -> Settings (account) -> Developer settings ->
#   Personal access tokens -> Fine-grained tokens -> Generate new
#     Resource owner:        sonawanedhiraj
#     Repository access:      Only select repositories -> openalgo
#     Repository permissions: Administration -> Read and write
#     Expiration:            shortest you can tolerate (rotate on expiry)
#   The token starts with github_pat_...
ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ── One-shot alternative (no auto re-register) ────────────────────────────
# If you instead use the short-lived registration token from
#   github.com/sonawanedhiraj/openalgo -> Settings -> Actions -> Runners ->
#   New self-hosted runner   (the value after `--token`)
# put it in RUNNER_TOKEN below and set EPHEMERAL: "false" in docker-compose.yml.
# That token expires in ~1h, so an ephemeral runner cannot re-register with it.
# RUNNER_TOKEN=
